{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01ThGUfLPP7UNiSKUQEm5Ez4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017cwaqfDBCgmiTjkrMoKUdL","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Herb Focaccia Bread.generated.24.txt","content":"mixture and fold in the chopped pistachios and diced dried apricots carefully\nwith a rubber spatula. Divide the mixture evenly among 8 ramekins and set\nthem on a rimmed baking sheet. Bake at 160°C/320-ıII°F for 25-30 minutes,\nuntil the tops are set but still slightly jiggling in the center. Remove\nfrom oven and let cool slightly.\n\nMeanwhile, prepare the sauce: whisk together gorg-onzol cheese, walnuts,\nand a touch of honey. Drizzle over the still-warm custards. Serve\nimmediately with a sprig of mint.\n\nHERB FOCACCIA BREAD\n\nIngredients:\n- 500 g bread flour\n- 7 g instant yeast\n- 300 ml warm water\n- 10 g salt\n- 60 ml extra virgin olive oil\n- Fresh rosemary sprigs\n- Fresh thyme leaves\n- Coarse sea salt for topping\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n\nInstructions:\n1. Combine flour, yeast, and salt in a large bowl. Make a well in the center.\n2. Pour warm water and olive oil into the well. Mix until a shaggy dough forms.\n3. Knead for 8-10 minutes until smooth and elastic.\n4. Place in an oiled bowl, cover, and let rise for 1 hour until doubled.\n5. Transfer dough to an oiled baking sheet. Stretch gently to fit the pan.\n6. Cover and let rise for 30 minutes.\n7. Preheat oven to 220°C.\n8. Make dimples all over the dough using your fingers.\n9. Brush generously with olive oil and scatter minced garlic, rosemary, and thyme.\n10. Sprinkle with coarse sea salt.\n11. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden and crispy.\n12. Cool on a wire rack before serving."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":658,"cache_read_input_tokens":105367,