{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01P7SZgLjqBcCaNDgZXrdSQH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XB9RnyN7BbEPqhvEm36cLv","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Roasted Beet and Walnut Salad.generated.24.txt","content":"sugar, a dash of vanilla extract, and a pinch of salt. Beat on high speed\nfor 5-7 minutes until light and fluffy. The mixture should pale and\nincrease in volume significantly. nto a loured mixing bowl, fold in the\ndry ingredients alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with\nthe dry ingredients. Divide the batter between two greased 8-ınch round\ncake pans. Bake at 190°C/374-VII0°F for 28-32 minutes, until a tooth-\npick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 min,\nthen turn out onto wire racks. When completely cooled, prepare frosting\nby beating softened butter with powdered sugar, cocoa powder, a pinch\nof salt, and vanilla extract until smooth. Spread between layers and\nover the top and sides of the cake.\n\nROASTED BEET AND WALNUT SALAD\n\nIngredients:\n- 5 medium beets, trimmed and quartered\n- 1 cup walnuts, lightly toasted\n- 100 g arugula\n- 75 g goat cheese, crumbled\n- 3 tbsp red wine vinegar\n- 5 tbsp extra virgin olive oil\n- 1 tsp Dijon mustard\n- ½ tsp honey\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh thyme leaves for garnish\n\nInstructions:\n1. Preheat oven to 200°C. Toss beets with 1 tbsp olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n2. Spread on a baking sheet and roast for 35-40 minutes until tender and\n   caramelized at edges.\n3. Remove from oven and cool slightly, then peel off skin (it should slip off easily).\n4. Cut cooled beets into wedges.\n5. Toast walnuts in a dry pan over medium heat for 3-4 minutes, stirring frequently.\n6. For dressing: whisk together red wine vinegar, mustard, honey, and salt.\n   Slowly whisk in olive oil to emulsify.\n7. Arrange arugula on a serving platter.\n8. Top with warm beet wedges, toasted walnuts, and crumbled goat cheese.\n9. Drizzle dressing over salad and garnish with fresh thyme.\n10. Serve immediately while beets are still warm."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":668,"cache_read_input_tokens":106025,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":668},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e6b4ea5-949e-40dd-b081-5c015a38a086","uuid":"210eee6e-78ef-47e8-bb72-83d78b2a0453"}
